Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_model_priority(25.10)                            set_model_priority(25.10)

Name
       set_model_priority - Allows you to define the priority order of models

Syntax
       set_model_priority

       [-help]

       [-objects <string>]

       [-priority_list <string>]

       Allows you to define the priority order of models.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage

       -objects <string>
              Specifies a list of library cells or library pins for which pri-
              ority is specified.

       -priority_list <string>
              Specifies a list of pin model priority.

              Default: {ecsm ccs nldm cdb udn}

Examples
       To    force    CCSN    to    be    used,   you   can   set   timing_li-
       brary_read_ccs_noise_data global variable to true  before  reading  the
       timing  libraries  and  then use the following command before using the
       update_glitch command:

       set_model_priority -priority_list ccs

Related Information
